    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-07T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="506"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/4–345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-07T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 7, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>646. The following for Johnson and Olsen from Department and War Refugee Board is
                    WRB 344, and refers to your numbers 1186 of March 28 and 1235 of April 3.<note
                        n="62" xml:id="d506fn62">Latter not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Report forwarded in your 1186 greatly appreciated.</p>
                <p>Department and Board approve the continuation of discussions designed solely to
                    save the lives of Jews and other victims of enemy oppression by means of relief
                    supplies or evacuation to safety. However, such discussions should be severed
                    immediately if, in the opinion of Minister Johnson, they become political in
                    nature.</p>
                <p>Board and Department leave entirely to discretion of Minister Johnson the
                    question of continuing the indirect contacts already made and the question of
                    Storch’s going to Berlin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
